vairables: ( look at nesicide.pro for defaults )

NESICIDE_CXXFLAGS
NESICIDE_LIBS

SDL_CXXFLAGS
SDL_LIBS

LUA_CXXFLAGS
LUA_LIBS

PREFIX
BINDIR

examples to build on linux:

PREFIX and/or BINDIR to the location you want to install if you run make install.
QMAKE_CXXFLAGS are optional if you want ot compile for your cpu.
QMAKE_LFLAGS needs rpath if any of the libraries are not in an ld path.
LIBS are needed if you dont set the individual libs as listed above.

qmake PREFIX=/tmp/test-nesicide QMAKE_CXXFLAGS="-march=athlon64 -O2 -pipe" QMAKE_LFLAGS="-Wl,-rpath,/tmp/test-nesicide/lib" LIBS="-L/tmp/test-nesicide/lib"

# this should work, i havent tested this yet.
qmake PREFIX=~/test-nesicide QMAKE_CXXFLAGS="-march=athlon64 -O2 -pipe" QMAKE_LFLAGS="-Wl,-rpath,~/test-nesicide/lib" LIBS="-L~/test-nesicide/lib"

if you choose to use qtcreator, open nesicide.pro project and select projects from the left side, then select show details under build steps.  there you can add additional arguments for the variables above.  editing this tiny box is kinda dumb, i suggest adding 1 or 2 options,quiting qtcreator and then
editing nesicide.pro.user, look for:
   <valuelist key="qmakeArgs" type="QVariantList">
    <value type="QString">QMAKE_CXXFLAGS=-march=athlon64 -O2 -pipe</value>
    <value type="QString">QMAKE_LFLAGS=-Wl,-rpath,/tmp/test-nesicide/lib</value>
    <value type="QString">LIBS=-L/tmp/test-nesicide/lib</value>
    <value type="QString">NESICIDE_LIBS=-L/tmp/test-nesicide/lib -lnesicide-emulator</value>
    <value type="QString">NESICIDE_CXXFLAGS=-I/tmp/test-nesicide/include</value>
   </valuelist>
